The <code><strong>MediaKeySystemAccess</strong></code> interface of the <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/API/EncryptedMediaExtensions_API">EncryptedMediaExtensions API</a> provides access to a Key System for decryption and/or a content protection provider. You can request an instance of this object using the <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/requestMediaKeySystemAccess" title="The Navigator.requestMediaKeySystemAccess() method returns a Promise which delivers a MediaKeySystemAccess object that can be used to access a particular media key system, which can in turn be used to create keys for decrypting a media stream. This method is part of the Encrypted Media Extensions API, which brings support for encrypted media and DRM-protected video to the web."><code>Navigator.requestMediaKeySystemAccess</code></a> method.